  order: 0,
  title: "<h2 id=\"h.cbwl91givwf\" style=\"padding-top:10pt;margin:0;color:#000000;padding-left:0;font-size:16pt;padding-bottom:0pt;line-height:1.5;page-break-after:avoid;font-family:&quot;Droid Serif&quot;;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:center;padding-right:0\"><span>1a. Welcome to the Party</span></h2>",
  content: "<p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">In your hands, you find an ornate envelope, rimmed with gold. The seal has been </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">broken</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;and the contents read. This is your invitation to the Midnight Murder Party, Reader. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">What is that, you ask? Well, allow </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">me to show you around and introduce you to tonight&rsquo;s hostess. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">You look up from the envelope and find that a beautiful banquet hall has materialized around you. Above your head, a vast chandelier casts little glimmers of light across the hall, the specks dancing playfully across the extravagant red and gold carpet and the deep mahogany paneled walls. Towering windows stare out of the front wall of the manor and into the black night outside. If it were morning, you might have seen a colorful garden sprawled out before the building, but the grandfather clock by the entrance arch hails that the time is now 11:53 at night. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">All along the walls, and even along the windowed side</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">, tables have been laid out with food and drink of every variety.</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;On one table, various bowls of pasta sit above tiny burners, all behind a sign with the word </span><span style=\"font-size:14pt;font-family:&quot;Dancing Script&quot;;font-weight:400\">Intestines</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;scrawled neatly in cursive. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">A heart is drawn next to the word.</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;Other tables contain juice-bleeding meat with the label </span><span style=\"font-size:14pt;font-family:&quot;Dancing Script&quot;;font-weight:400\">Human Flesh</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;or bright red fruit punch with the label </span><span style=\"font-size:14pt;font-family:&quot;Dancing Script&quot;;font-weight:400\">Blood</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;or even peeled grapes labeled </span><span style=\"font-size:14pt;font-family:&quot;Dancing Script&quot;;font-weight:400\">Eyeballs</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">. All manner of food and drink decorates these tables, flowing with red tablecloths, in anticipation of the guests&rsquo; arrivals.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">On the far end of the banquet hall, opposite the grandfather clock, the room opens up into a smaller, pentagonal tea room with huge slab-like windows </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">gazing out into the world beyond.</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;A young woman looks out at the blackness from that room, h</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">er</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;fiery orange-red hair falling down over her shoulders in voluminous curls. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">She wears a billowing purple and black dress that clings tightly to her torso before cinching at her narrow waist and expanding again until it nearly skims the floor</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">. As she turns to face you, her eyes widen and she jumps back with a gasp. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Oh, my. You startled me!&rdquo; she exclaims, letting a well-manicured hand rest over her heart. A wide grin breaks out and lights up her whole face. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s been a while since anyone&rsquo;s managed to startle </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">me</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">. Ahahaha! You must be a Reader, then. Seriously, those Creators never have you guys knock. They just pop you into existence wherever they please! Oh, but it makes everything so much more lively sometimes. Once, this Reader just went and popped in right in the middle of&mdash;&rdquo; She pauses and clears her throat, resuming a pretense of formality. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Oh, but where are my manners? I haven&rsquo;t even introduced myself. My name is Arlene. I am the hostess of this Midnight Murder Party. As you can see, no one else is here yet. It&rsquo;s only 11:57, so you&rsquo;re a little early. That&rsquo;s alright, though. I&rsquo;ll use this time to explain the rules.&rdquo;</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">She gestures across the great hall towards a golden plaque embedded above the entranceway. &ldquo;The rules are engraved on there in case you ever forget, but they&rsquo;re pretty simple, so you should be fine. Rule number one.&rdquo; A devious smile plays across her face as she leans in. &ldquo;You </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">will</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;be murdered. Possibly multiple times. There&rsquo;s no limit to how many times you can die here. In fact, we could just kill you over and over all night long if we wanted to!&rdquo; She throws her head back in cackling laughter before putting a dainty hand over her mouth. &ldquo;Oops! Sorry about that. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">Ahaha</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">. Rule number two. If you die, it&rsquo;s your turn to tell the next story. We all take turns telling stories. If you die, you&rsquo;re up.&rdquo; She pauses and looks at you seriously. There is no humor left in her face. &ldquo;Rule number three. I&rsquo;ll warn you right now, if you don&rsquo;t think you&rsquo;re up for it, then now is the time to leave. Rule number three is what breaks most of them. What&rsquo;ll it be?&rdquo; Even though she couldn&rsquo;t be older than twenty-five, weary lines of age seem to appear on her face as she surveys you, silently questioning your resolve. She waits only a moment longer. </span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;I guess that decides it then. Rule number three is&hellip;&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;It&rsquo;ll be fun!&rdquo; She bursts into smiles again and snorts laughter. &ldquo;I had you going, didn&rsquo;t I? I totally did! Ahahahaha! Oh man! That was </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">gold</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">!&rdquo; She wipes the tears from her eyes and tries to regain her composure, still letting little fits of giggling slip. &ldquo;Oh, but I actually should warn you, given the nature of rule number one, things tend to get&hellip; well, a little messy around here, and the stories we tell can be rather disturbing. So if you&rsquo;re squeamish, fair warning!&rdquo; Something catches her eye behind you, and she exclaims, &ldquo;Hey, look! If it isn&rsquo;t Marc!&rdquo;</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">A lanky kid strolls into the room with his hands stuffed into the pockets of his jeans. The purple, skull-checkered </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">shirt hanging from his shoulders</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;looks out of place in the elaborate dining hall, but he doesn&rsquo;t seem to notice. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">His eyelids hang at half-mast, as if he couldn&rsquo;t imagine a more boring place to be, but his smile is amiable.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;How&rsquo;s things, Arly?&rdquo; He asks through a toothpick sticking out from between his front teeth.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Well, you </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">would</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;know if you bothered to stop by once in a while,&rdquo; Arlene </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">huff</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">s. &ldquo;I haven&rsquo;t seen you since the last party! I do hope you&rsquo;ve enjoyed the party favor I left you with last time, by the way.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Marc gives her a dumb look and shifts the toothpick between his teeth. &ldquo;Party favor?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Oh, nevermind,&rdquo; Arlene sighs. &ldquo;More importantly, why on Earth do you have a toothpick in your mouth?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Had somethin&rsquo; stuck in my teeth,&rdquo; he says, diverting his eyes. He plucks it out of his mouth and flicks it into the nearest wastebin. His cheeks have gotten a little red.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Of course you did.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Well, forget that,&rdquo; Marc interjects, going redder still. &ldquo;I want to introduce you to my little bro. Come on out and say hi, Aidan.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">A wide-eyed face appears from behind Marc. The kid only reaches midway up his torso. Unlike his older brother, Aidan is garbed in a black suit with a white button down shirt and a black tie that cinches around his neck just a little too tightly. Marc loosens this for him. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">The kid stares at Arlene for a moment, his light brown hair falling clumsily into his eyes, </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">before shaking his head, squeezing his eyes shut, and ducking behind Marc again.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Sorry about that,&rdquo; Marc says, placing a light hand on his brother&rsquo;s head, &ldquo;Aidan&rsquo;s a bit shy.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;That&rsquo;s quite alright,&rdquo;</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;Arlene responds. &ldquo;I would like to introduce you both to a rather unexpected guest. We have a Reader with us tonight.&rdquo; She turns towards you, a puzzled expression coming over her face. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Oh my, where has he gone? Or was it a she? I can never tell with Readers.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Marc raises an eyebrow. &ldquo;You messin&rsquo; with us, Arly?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Not at all. There was a Reader here just before you came in.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Gotcha.&rdquo; Marc grins. Aidan peeks out from behind him, squinting at the spot Arlene is looking at. &ldquo;Well, our Reader friend has probably just stopped being visible to us for a while. Wouldn&rsquo;t be a first. I&rsquo;m sure he&mdash;or she, I guess&mdash;is still in here somewhere.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Very true.&rdquo; Arlene claps her hands together. &ldquo;Perhaps our friend will show</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">up again later. Until then...&rdquo; She peers over Marc&rsquo;s shoulder and smiles at someone behind him under the archway. &ldquo;It seems that everyone has arrived. And just on time.&rdquo; She glances sidelong at the grandfather clock as Marc turns around to see who arrived behind him. Arlene continues. &ldquo;My friends, it is my pleasure to welcome all of you. Now&hellip;&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">In this moment, several things happen simultaneously. The clock by the entranceway chimes midnight. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">Marc&rsquo;s head cracks open and bursts, </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">blooming into crimson flowers</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;across the wall, floor, and clock face with a tremendous </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">boom</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;that echoes through the grand hall. </span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Chunks of clotted, brown hair and brain splatter and stick to the walls. Aidan screams and hides under a table. And Arlene raises her hands into the air and exclaims:</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.15;text-indent:36pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;orphans:2;widows:2;height:11pt;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\"></span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Let the Midnight Murder Party begin!&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.15;text-indent:36pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;orphans:2;widows:2;height:11pt;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\"></span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">A piercing laugh comes from the entrance to the room.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Kyehehehe! You got him, you got him good!&rdquo; A girl, perhaps a few years older than Aidan, stands in the entranceway behind Marc&rsquo;s corpse as it collapses. Her piercing, emerald eyes stare out from the bloody mask that has splattered across her face, wide awake despite the grey bags that hang under them. She beams at Arlene, not minding the dripping blood. &ldquo;You&rsquo;re the best, Arlene!&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">The hostess curtsies. &ldquo;Why, thank you, Marissa. And look at that nice dress you wore today. My opening fireworks seem to have made quite a mess of it. My apologies!&rdquo; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;No worries,&rdquo; Marissa says, regarding the mess that has splattered across the front of her outfit with some amusement. Her</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;dress is black with red frills, tied neatly around the waist with an enormous red bow. Below the bow, the dress puffs out until the knees where it meets with white stockings (now speckled with red) that eventually disappear into a pair of black shoes with golden buckles</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">. She pats little clumps of brain off the dress, and they land on the floor with a </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">squick</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;sound. &ldquo;Gross.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">She wrings some blood out of her hair, twirls the strand in front of her eyes, and smiles at the reddish-brown color before letting it fall back onto her shoulder. With her hands on her hips, she looks down to study the mess that used to be Marc&rsquo;s head. After a moment of prodding brains and skull around with her toe, her eyes light up, and she bends over to scoop up one of Marc&rsquo;s marbled brown eyes between her fingers. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Marc has such nice eyes. Too bad they&rsquo;re attached to the rest of him.&rdquo; </span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">She snorts a laugh and holds the eye out in front of her, grinning. Arlene walks over, stepping gingerly over Marc&rsquo;s corpse. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Very true,&rdquo; she says, poking it with her pinky to examine the underside. &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve never noticed.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;It&rsquo;s &lsquo;cuz that dummy keeps his eyes half closed all the time. We&rsquo;ll have to explode his head more often.&rdquo; Marissa giggles and stuffs the eyeball into her pocket.</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;&ldquo;I&rsquo;m keeping this.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Perhaps we will do some arts and crafts later,&rdquo; Arlene suggests. &ldquo;You could make it into a necklace.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;No way! I want an eyeball ring.&rdquo; The girls look at each other and burst into laughter.</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;Aidan pokes his head out from under the table across the room, and Marissa stops </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">laughing.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Why&rsquo;s he lookin&rsquo; at me like that? It&rsquo;s weirding me out.&rdquo; She glances at Aidan. &ldquo;Quit starin&rsquo; at me, kid. It&rsquo;s weird.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Arlene chuckles. &ldquo;You say &lsquo;kid&rsquo; as if you aren&rsquo;t one yourself, Marissa.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Hey, I&rsquo;m not a </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">kid</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">. I&rsquo;m a </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">teen</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">. I&rsquo;m thir</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">teen</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Of course. How could I have forgotten?&rdquo; Arlene chuckles again.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Marissa, pouting, turns back to Aidan, who has retreated behind the red tablecloth again, peeking out with only one eye. &ldquo;And you, stop gawkin&rsquo; at me. Creep.&rdquo; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">A moment of silence passes between them. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Hi.&rdquo; Aidan blurts and disappears again.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Arlene grins at Marissa.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;What?&rdquo; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Oh, nothing.&rdquo; Arlene sings, still grinning.</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;&ldquo;In any case, it seems everyone is here, so why don&rsquo;t we all head over to the tea room?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">Arlene snaps her fingers and all the stray pieces of Marc begin to slide and ooze towards his collapsed body. The skull clicks together like a puzzle as brain and blood slide into the openings and reassemble themselves inside.</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;Flesh, muscle, and skin reattach to the skull like pieces of wrapping paper being torn in reverse.</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;Teeth rattle along the floor and socket themselves firmly within the gum. One eyeball pops back into place. The other struggles to escape Marissa&rsquo;s pocket and follow the trail of blood streaming off of her outfit back to Marc, but she keeps a firm hold. It all stops and Marc sits up, coughing and sputtering, trying to pull oxygen into his lungs. He looks around, dazed.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Huh...&rdquo;</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;His remaining eye snaps wide open. &ldquo;Wait a sec! Arly, </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">that</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;was your party favor? I&rsquo;ve been running around with a </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">bomb</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;in my head since last time?&rdquo; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Arlene smiles pleasantly. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;You&rsquo;re ridiculous,&rdquo; Marc continues. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">He pauses with a quizzical expression. &ldquo;Huh. Everything looks kinda&hellip; off. Weird.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;It&rsquo;s probably just your imagination,&rdquo; Marissa says, patting Marc on the back. &ldquo;Hi, by the way.&rdquo; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;How&rsquo;s it going, Marissa? I would&rsquo;ve said hi earlier, but </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">someone</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">,&rdquo; he casts Arlene a reproachful glance, &ldquo;blew my head off before I could say anything.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Yeah, it was sweet. You shoulda </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">seen</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;it!</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;Arlene&rsquo;s traps are the best. She might even be able to catch </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">me</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;in one of them. Kyehehehe.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;If I don&rsquo;t kill you first,&rdquo; Marc retorts, feigning a lunge at the girl. She dodges nimbly to the side.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Not gonna happen!&rdquo; Marissa sticks her tongue out at Marc, and he laughs.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;We&rsquo;ll see, now won&rsquo;t we?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Ahem.&rdquo; Arlene interrupts the banter. &ldquo;Shall we move into the tea room to begin the first story?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">The group relocates to the pentagonal, windowed room appended to the end of the hall. Three chairs have been set around a large table in the center of the room which is covered in different types of sweets. Marissa piles a plate high with cookies before plopping down in a seat next to Arlene. Marc sits across from them, his brother peeking out from behind his chair at Marissa.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-em. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Hi.&rdquo; Aidan blurts and disappears again.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Arlene grins at Marissa.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;What?&rdquo; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Oh, nothing.&rdquo; Arlene sings, still grinning.</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;&ldquo;In any case, it seems everyone is here, so why don&rsquo;t we all head over to the tea room?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">Arlene snaps her fingers and all the stray pieces of Marc begin to slide and ooze towards his collapsed body. The skull clicks together like a puzzle as brain and blood slide into the openings and reassemble themselves inside.</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;Flesh, muscle, and skin reattach to the skull like pieces of wrapping paper being torn in reverse.</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;Teeth rattle along the floor and socket themselves firmly within the gum. One eyeball popsback into place. The other struggles to escape Marissa&rsquo;s pocket and follow the trail of blood streaming off of her outfit back to Marc, but she keeps a firm hold. It all stops and Marc sits up, coughing and sputtering, trying to pull oxygen into his lungs. He looks around, dazed.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Huh...&rdquo;</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;His remaining eye snaps wide open. &ldquo;Wait a sec! Arly, </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">that</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;was your party favor? I&rsquo;ve been running around with a </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">bomb</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;in my head since last time?&rdquo; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Arlene smiles pleasantly. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;You&rsquo;re ridiculous,&rdquo; Marc continues. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">He pauses with a quizzical expression. &ldquo;Huh. Everything looks kinda&hellip; off. Weird.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;It&rsquo;s probably just your imagination,&rdquo; Marissa says, patting Marc on the back. &ldquo;Hi, by the way.&rdquo; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;How&rsquo;s it going, Marissa? I would&rsquo;ve said hi earlier, but </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">someone</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">,&rdquo; he casts Arlene a reproachful glance, &ldquo;blew my head off before I could say anything.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Yeah, it was sweet. You shoulda </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">seen</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;it!</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;Arlene&rsquo;s traps are the best. She might even be able to catch </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">me</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;in one of them. Kyehehehe.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;If I don&rsquo;t kill you first,&rdquo; Marc retorts, feigning a lunge at the girl. She dodges nimbly to the side.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Not gonna happen!&rdquo; Marissa sticks her tongue out at Marc, and he laughs.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;We&rsquo;ll see, now won&rsquo;t we?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Ahem.&rdquo; Arlene interrupts the banter. &ldquo;Shall we move into the tea room to begin the first story?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">The group relocates to the pentagonal, windowed room appended to the end of the hall. Three chairs have been set around a large table in the center of the room which is covered in different types of sweets. Marissa piles a plate high with cookies before plopping down in a seat next to Arlene. Marc sits across from them, his brother peeking out from behind his chair at Marissa.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">A</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">rlene summons a servant from the kitchen, a petite girl, about Marc&rsquo;s age, wearing a black tuxedo with her blonde hair tied in a ponytail low on the back of her neck and her bangs hanging neatly on either side of her face, one side held up by a thin, blue hair clip.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Would you please bring out another chair for Marc&rsquo;s brother,&rdquo; Arlene asks the servant before pausing for a moment. &ldquo;Actually, make that two chairs, just in case our Reader friend decides to show up again.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">The girl nods politely and makes to leave. &nbsp;&ldquo;One more thing,&rdquo; Arlene says, calling the girl back. She beckons her closer with one curled finger and whispers something into the servant&rsquo;s ear. The girl nods, her sheepish expression turning into a soft grin, and leaves the room. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Hey, Arly,&rdquo; Marc says once the servant is out of sight. &ldquo;She new here? She doesn&rsquo;t look like your usual servants.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Yes indeed.&rdquo; Arlene smiles. &ldquo;Her name is April.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Marc looks at the door the servant disappeared through. &ldquo;That&rsquo;s a nice name,&rdquo; he says after a moment. &ldquo;Where&rsquo;d you find her?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Just floating about. She had nowhere to go, so I employed her.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">Two new servants&mdash;both tall, expressionless, and uncannily identical to the point of looking like they had been made with a cookie-cutter&mdash;enter the hall and place the additional chairs around the large table.</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;Next to each chair, there is a smaller table where a decorative, white teacup is placed on a saucer for each guest. April reappears in the hall with a tea cart and begins filling their cups. Marc speaks up.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&ldquo;Well, I guess it&rsquo;s about time to get this party started. I&rsquo;ve thought up some good ones for tonight, so here it </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">goes.&rdquo; Arlene</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;leans forward in her seat, wide-eyed. Marissa pops a cookie into her mouth and munches away. Aidan peeks out a little farther from behind Marc&rsquo;s seat. Marc continues. &ldquo;The title of this story is&hellip;&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
  releaseDate: "2018-03-09 15:00:00 UTC",
  authorsNote: "",
  isInteractive: false,
  interactiveData: "",
  interactiveUrl: ""
)

Entry.create(
  chapterId: 1,
  level: 1,
  order: 1,
  title: "<h2 id=\"h.8gu8hj2twkcv\" style=\"padding-top:10pt;margin:0;color:#000000;padding-left:0;font-size:16pt;padding-bottom:0pt;line-height:1.5;page-break-after:avoid;font-family:&quot;Droid Serif&quot;;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:center;padding-right:0\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:16pt;font-family:&quot;Droid Serif&quot;;font-style:normal\">1b. Heat Wave</span></h2>",
  content: "<p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">David woke up at a quarter to six to kick off his covers. Today was going to be a hot one. He flipped his pillow over and placed his cheek against the cool side, except this morning it wasn&rsquo;t much better than the side he had been sleeping on. Not at all. He sat up groggily and wiped the sticky sweat from his brow with the back of his arm. The room felt oddly quiet, and it occurred to him that the air conditioner had stopped&mdash;had probably blown a fuse during the night. He tapped his phone, and the screen came to life. One hundred and one. That&rsquo;s what the weather app on his home screen told him. At a quarter to six in the morning, with the sun barely peeking over the horizon, it was already a hundred and one degrees out. He groaned, rolled over, and fell back into a turbulent sleep. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When he woke up again, his first thought was that he couldn&rsquo;t breathe. He gasped in an unsatisfying breath of hot and heavy air and didn&rsquo;t feel much better. The air conditioner still hung dead in the window. With more than a little effort, he hoisted himself off the bed, leaving behind a body shaped dark spot in the blue sheets where sweat had soaked in. He made his way to the kitchen.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;A middle-aged woman slouched over the table, one hand propping up her cheek and the other fanning her face with a paper plate. Her brown hair fell in damp clumps from her head as a steady stream of sweat poured down her face, tracing the usually unnoticeable contours of age.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Mom, why isn&rsquo;t the air on? It&rsquo;s hot as&mdash;&rdquo; David paused, finding the atmosphere too much. It wasn&rsquo;t humid, but the sheer heat felt just as bad in his throat. He took a slow breath. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s really hot.&rdquo; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">She glanced up, and David winced. Her face sagged noticeably, the way elderly people&rsquo;s skin falls away from the flesh and bone as if it no longer feels any need to hang on. &ldquo;The power&rsquo;s out&hellip; for the whole block.&rdquo; She turned away and looked out the window, dragging in a slow breath. &ldquo;Maybe for the whole city.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Oh, come on,&rdquo; David grumbled. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s like&mdash;&rdquo; He looked at his phone. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s 117 degrees? Is that even possible?&rdquo; But he supposed it must be. After all, it </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">felt</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;like 117 degrees. &ldquo;Screw this. I&rsquo;m going to the pool.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">He changed into his bathing suit, grabbed a towel from the hall closet, and walked past the kitchen to the front door. &ldquo;Mom,&rdquo; he called. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m heading out. You should find a way to cool off too. You don&rsquo;t look too good.&rdquo; The door slammed behind him.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Even wearing just a tank top, swim trunks and flip-flops, it felt like he was baking in the sun. The sky shone blue and clear, all the clouds burnt away by the wavering yellow-orange orb still approaching its high point in the sky. He passed an ice cream truck, surrounded by whining kids, pushing and shoving to get their turn. The parents seemed too exhausted to care, hanging in place, their hands shielding their eyes from the sun, some even holding umbrellas to shade themselves and telling their kids to hurry up. One kid finally got his treat: a red, white and blue rocket pop that David himself had loved when he was a few years younger. The kid pulled back from the group, clinging to his new treat, and, when he had made it a safe distance from the jealous eyes of the other kids, tore off the wrapper. David thought the face the kid made might have been the most disappointed thing he had ever seen. The pop was already half-melted when the wrapper came off, and the gooey top trickled down in smears of red and white, off the bottom of the pop and onto the ground. David passed by.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Once on his way to the pool, the tip of his flip-flop caught on the ground and folded under itself. He stubbed his toe on the searing asphalt. It left a blister.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">By the time the pool gates came into view, the air was wavering in front of David. It gave everything a surreal appearance, as if he were looking at a mirage in a desert instead of a real place. He pulled in another labored breath of the thin, dry air that felt like sand in his throat. A wave of dizziness nearly brought him to his knees, and he thought hazily that it must have reached 130 degrees. His phone screen said 141, then updated to 153.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">He walked through the gates and groaned. The pool was packed, well past allowed capacity, but no one seemed to care. Even the lifeguard was in the pool instead of on her stand. David approached the edge. People pressed against each other in the giant tub, some people on top of others, intertwined in all sorts of strange and unnatural ways. There was no room for David.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;&lsquo;Scuse me, could I get in?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">No one looked at him. They all looked dazed, staring blankly at the sky or the water or the sweaty back of the person pressed in front of them. Only a fat man with a chin-strap beard who was balding on the top of his head glanced up. &ldquo;What&rsquo;s it look like, smart guy? There&rsquo;s no room. Go away.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;C&rsquo;mon, there&rsquo;s nowhere else to&mdash;&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;You deaf kid? There ain&rsquo;t no room,&rdquo; the fat man grunted. His skin sagged with the heat. Everyone in the pool seemed to be sagging. David thought of the rocket pop. The little pockets of water surrounding the people had a strange hue to them&mdash;skin colored. &nbsp;&ldquo;Anyway, the water ain&rsquo;t even cool. It&rsquo;s too damn </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">hot</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;in here.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Ugh, fine.&rdquo; David groaned, turning around. He wasn&rsquo;t sure where to go from here, but he thought the park might be the best bet. It had shade at least. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">There was no one on the roads now. A couple people sat out on their front porches fanning themselves weakly, mouths agape and tongues lolling out like </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">a dog&rsquo;s.</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;David thought one old woman had been dripping from the porch-swing onto the wooden floor below. It must have been sweat or something, but with the way his vision was dancing in the heat, it looked almost as if she had been melting. He could&rsquo;ve sworn he saw a peachy-grey puddle spreading underneath her. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">He turned left and continued another couple blocks until the park came into view. His legs felt wobbly and threatened to give out, but he pushed forward, wiping the thick sweat out of his eyes with his forearm. Instead of helping, it felt as if he were just smearing more of that creamy sweat into his eyes, so he opted to just blink it out instead.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">His flip-flop landed in a puddle on the sidewalk in front of the park, splashing the molten, brownish water onto the top of his foot. He tried to reel back from the burning puddle, but this time his legs did give out, and he landed on his butt, expecting a thud but instead hearing a splat, as if someone had dropped jello on the floor. His pants and the back of his shirt felt wet, and he thought he had fallen into a second puddle. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">But he could only see the one in front of him. Thick, sticky brown with splotches of black and a couple little red chunks floating inside it. Around the edge of the mess, hair stuck to the sidewalk in clots. Some of that hair also stuck to the red blobs in the puddle. David&rsquo;s mind screamed the word </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">dog</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;before he noticed the collar submerged in the soup. Even as his mind tried to explain what had happened here&mdash;a car had hit it, or maybe some sick asshole had done this, or&mdash;the word </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">melted</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;rang out strong, just as the word </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">dog</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;had a second before.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">He leaned forward and hurled into the puddle, dark yellowish bile swirling in with the brown. Then there was another voice.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Hey, kid!&rdquo; It gasped, slurring the words so that </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">kid</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&nbsp;sounded more like </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">kuuud</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">. &ldquo;You can help me? So </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">hot</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">, right? I think my head, the heat&hellip; it&rsquo;s messin&rsquo;, ya know?&rdquo; David lifted his head, blinking hard to clear the sweat&mdash;which didn&rsquo;t feel like sweat&mdash;from his eyes. There was a man stumbling towards him, arms outstretched and dripping onto the pavement. A smeared trail followed behind where the man dragged his feet. &ldquo;Ya got some cool, eh?&rdquo; The man droned. &ldquo;Just little bit, uh huh.&rdquo; David&rsquo;s eyes widened. The top of the man&rsquo;s head looked like the gruesome top of the rocket pop, sagging and melting, pouring red and grey and peach down the side of his face and onto his pink t-shirt. &ldquo;Comeonman, just got fan or some-tin. Keep thuh het uff.&rdquo; Another chunk of grey sloshed from the man&rsquo;s skull onto the ground.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">David was on his feet, spinning on his heels, and before the man could say anything else, David took off running. He heard the splashes against the concrete behind him and ignored it. He sucked in another wave of hot air and found himself coughing up thick, pinkish red. Then he was passing by the pool again. He glanced in and didn&rsquo;t see the people anymore. The water had turned a muddy red, some pockets closer to peach, others darker, but it all looked lumpy, like nearly melted ice cream. Except it was boiling. Violent bubbles burst through the surface of the gelatinous goop, sending it exploding outward onto the deck around the pool and the grass past that.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">David closed his eyes and kept going, hearing only the sickening squelching sounds under his own feet. He opened his eyes long enough to see the ice cream truck, sagging and pooling around what used to be tires, and the surrounding human-colored puddles trickling lazily into it.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">He fell to the ground with a splash that he didn&rsquo;t think he liked. His thoughts slowed to a crawl. Something was wrong with his head, but he didn&rsquo;t know what. It felt somehow&hellip; itchy? He reached to scratch his temple and felt the softening fingernails scoop some of it away. It didn&rsquo;t seem important. For a moment, he wondered vaguely if his mother had ever gone out to cool off. Then his mind seeped out across the pavement. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.15;text-indent:36pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;orphans:2;widows:2;height:11pt;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\"></span></p>",
  releaseDate: "2018-03-16 15:00:00 UTC",
  authorsNote: "",
  isInteractive: false,
  interactiveData: "",
  interactiveUrl: ""
)

Entry.create(
  chapterId: 1,
  level: 1,
  order: 2,
  title: "<h2 id=\"h.94rhzxtqoies\" style=\"padding-top:10pt;margin:0;color:#000000;padding-left:0;font-size:16pt;padding-bottom:0pt;line-height:1.5;page-break-after:avoid;font-family:&quot;Droid Serif&quot;;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:center;padding-right:0\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:16pt;font-family:&quot;Droid Serif&quot;;font-style:normal\">1c. Welcome to the Party - Outro</span></h2>",
  content: "<p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">Marc leans back in his chair, stretching his arms behind his head with a sigh. &ldquo;That&rsquo;s it. The end.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&ldquo;What a perfectly strange tale to begin the night!&rdquo; Arlene exclaims, clapping her hands together.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&ldquo;Well, you know me,&rdquo; Marc responds grinning. &ldquo;What did you think, Marissa?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&ldquo;Coulda used more blood,&rdquo; she says, feigning a bored expression, &ldquo;but I guess it was a&rsquo;ight.&rdquo; She smirks. &ldquo;The boiling pool of humans was pretty nasty.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Oh yeah? Was that a compliment from the queen of gore herself?&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Don&rsquo;t let it go to your head, dumb-butt.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Umm&hellip;&rdquo; Aidan squeaks from behind Marc&rsquo;s chair. &ldquo;I liked the dog puddle.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Dog puddle!&rdquo; Arlene cries across the table, bursting into laughter. &ldquo;Oh, man. That could be the name of a hardcore band, don&rsquo;t you think?&rdquo; She puts her hands on her hips, lowers her eyebrows in a mock angry face, and her voice becomes lower and gruff. </span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">Hey, man. We&rsquo;re Dog Puddle, and we&rsquo;re here to rock the house &lsquo;cuz we&rsquo;re so hardcore. Urrrrgghhh.</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&rdquo; </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Sounds like a band Marc would listen to,&rdquo; Marissa snorts. </span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Hey,&rdquo; Marc says. &ldquo;Dog Puddle has some solid lyrics. And don&rsquo;t even get me started on their polyrhythms!&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-weight:400\">&ldquo;Poly-</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:italic;font-weight:400\">whats</span><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">?&rdquo; Marissa says. Arlene looks lost.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Jeez, you guys are musically hopeless. Well, nevermind.&rdquo; Marc pauses and blinks hard a couple times. &ldquo;Ya know, I still think everything looks kinda off. Does my eye look alright to you guys? Feels a little weird.&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Well, I don&rsquo;t see anything wrong with it,&rdquo; Arlene offers, smiling.</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;text-indent:36pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:12pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;font-style:normal\">&ldquo;Yeah, that&rsquo;s right!&rdquo; Marissa chimes in, stuffing her hand in her pocket and rolling Marc&rsquo;s eye between her fingers. &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t see anything at all!&rdquo;</span></p><p style=\"padding:0;margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;line-height:1.15;orphans:2;widows:2;height:11pt;text-align:left\"><span style=\"color:#000000;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;font-size:11pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;;font-style:normal\"></span></p>",
  releaseDate: "2018-03-23 15:00:00 UTC",
  authorsNote: "",
  isInteractive: false,
  interactiveData: "",
  interactiveUrl: ""
)
